  • Method Details

    • load

      public void load​(Package[] arr)
      Test if each Package in array is: 1. not null 2. tracking number and weight are correct 3. trunk[] is not full It first checks if there is an empty spot, then assigns the package if it's valid. If truck is full, and there are still packages unloaded, it will throw an exception.
      Parameters:
      pkg - Package we want to load

    • unload

      public void unload​(int d)
      This method removes the package wanted, as well as rearrange the packages in the array if the removed package was in the middle of the array.
      Parameters:
      d - The index of the package the user wants to remove.
